## Modern Angular Guidelines

Use current Angular patterns (v16+).

- Prefer standalone components, directives, and pipes.
- Always use single-file components.
- Default export component classes.
- Use signals for local state when appropriate; avoid unnecessary RxJS for simple state.
- Use the new control flow syntax (`@if`, `@for`, `@switch`) instead of structural directives.
- Favor `inject()` over constructor injection when it keeps code cleaner.
- Use `provideHttpClient()` and `provideRouter()` in bootstrap instead of module-based providers.
- Enforce `rxResource` for data fetching in services and components.
- Keep components lean: push data access and business logic into services.
- Prefer `OnPush` change detection; use `signal`/`computed` to minimize manual `markForCheck`.
- Use `DestroyRef` or `takeUntilDestroyed` for cleanup in RxJS streams.
- Avoid `NgModule` unless required for legacy or third-party integrations.
- Prefer `afterRenderEffect` over `ngOnInit` for component initialization
